description: Borrowed from Spanish junco (“reed, rush”), from Latin iuncus (“reed, rush”), ultimately from Proto-Indo-European *yoy-ni-. Doublet of juncus and junk.

entries.meaning: Any bird of the genus Junco, which includes several species of North American sparrow.
(obsolete) The common reed bunting (Emberiza schoeniclus), a bird found in Europe and much of the Palearctic.
